# Troubleshooting Quick Reference (Top 10)

## 1) `no matching Route53 Hosted Zone found`
- Cause: zone doesn’t exist in account.
- Fix: create hosted zone first, or use ALB DNS for non-prod.

## 2) `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` in UI tests
- Cause: app not running on `127.0.0.1:3000`.
- Fix: run app first or configure Playwright `webServer`.

## 3) Playwright CI: `.../health is already used`
- Cause: app started twice (`npm start &` + Playwright `webServer`).
- Fix: remove manual start/wait from workflow.

## 4) `Cannot find package 'mysql2/promise'`
- Cause: missing app dependency.
- Fix: install `mysql2`, commit lockfile, rerun tests.

## 5) EKS node group launch/join failures
- Cause: node size/subnet/bootstrap mismatch.
- Fix: adjust instance type/capacity and subnet config, reapply module 02.

## 6) Argo Helm release timeout
- Cause: insufficient cluster capacity / failed prior release.
- Fix: increase nodes, replace tainted helm release, reapply module 03.

## 7) Argo app `Unknown` or resources pruned
- Cause: manifests missing/changed in Git path.
- Fix: restore manifests in `apps/webapp/k8s`, refresh/sync app.

## 8) Argo sync invalid Deployment (`DB_HOST` as container name)
- Cause: DB vars put under `containers`, not `env`.
- Fix: move `DB_*` entries to `containers[0].env`.

## 9) API `503 Database is not configured` or `ETIMEDOUT`
- Cause: missing DB env, placeholder password, or RDS ingress blocked.
- Fix: set real secret values, wire env vars, allow MySQL ingress (`3306`) from app network path.

## 10) Destroy fails on VPC/IGW/Subnet dependencies
- Cause: leftover ELB ENIs / non-default SGs / mapped public IPs.
- Fix: delete classic ELB and dependent ENIs/SGs, rerun destroy.
